data.chText: 士兵们被命令返回营房。
data.enText: The troops were ordered back to barracks .
any large ugly building or buildings

word_means: barrack的第三人称单数和复数

means: 给(所支持的人或队)加油
barrack的第三人称单数和复数

value.def: A barracks is a building or group of buildings where soldiers or other members of the armed forces live and work. 'Barracks' is the singular and plural form.

example.ex: ...an army barracks in the north of the city.

value.def: If people in an audience barrack public speakers or performers, they interrupt them, for example by making rude remarks.

example.ex: Fans gained more enjoyment barracking him than cheering on the team...
example.tran: 球迷一个劲儿地嘘他，兴头远胜于为球队加油。

example.ex: President Alan Garcia was barracked by the right wing opposition.
example.tran: 阿兰·加西亚总统遭右翼反对派喝倒彩。

example.ex: He was affected badly by the barracking that he got from the crowd.
example.tran: 人群中的一片嘘声令他大受影响。
